LINUX
======

1. In Linux, how do you attach and detach a filesystem?.
	use mount & umount cmmands
	Ex:- mount /filesystem1 /filesystem2
	Ex:- umount /filesystem1 /filesystem2
2. How do you print the last 15 lines of a file in Linux?
	#tail -n 15 filename.log
3. How do you enable passwordless authentication between two servers?
	1. Server A (source) - 
	#ssh-keygen -t rsa -b 4096
	#ssh-copy-id user@Server B or #cat ~/.ssh/id_rsa.pub | ssh user@serverB 'mkdir -p ~/.ssh && cat >> ~/.ssh/authorized_keys && chmod 600 ~/.ssh/authorized_keys' 
		-> Enter the password for once
	2. To test from server A
	#ssh user@ServerB  -> login without password
4. Disk space is full on a production server — what do you do?
- Check disk usage 		#df -h
- Check large files/directories #du -sh /* 2>/dev/null | sort -hr | head -20
- Clear Old logs 		#rm -rf /var/log/old_log_file.log
- Preventive Tip: Set up logrotate.
5. A process is consuming high CPU — how do you troubleshoot it?
- Check top CPU-consuming processes:	#top
- Get process details:			#lsof -p <PID> or #strace -p <PID> or #pidstat -o <PID>
- Kill or restart process if needed:	#kill -9 <PID>
6. A server is not reachable via SSH — how would you diagnose it?
- Check network connectivity:				#ping <server-ip>
- Check port						#telnet <server-ip> 22
- From remote system (if you have other access):	#systemctl status sshd or #journalctl -xe | grep ssh
- Firewall check:					#iptables -L	
7. How do you schedule regular backups using cron?
- to edit 	#crontab -e
- * * * * * /bin/startup.sh >> /var/log/backup.log 2>&1
- to verify 	#crontab -l
